# Quote Video Pipeline

Scrapes Arabic wisdom quotes, narrates them with text-to-speech, and lays
the narration over a background video to produce short quote videos.

## Files

| File             | Purpose                                                              |
|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `scraper.py`     | Scrapes quotes from the source page into `quotes.csv` (was `scrap.py`) |
| `tts.py`         | Text-to-speech helper using edge-tts (was `audio.py`)                |
| `video.py`       | Merges an audio file onto a background video (was `vedu.py`)         |
| `pipeline.py`    | Orchestrates: pick next quote → TTS → merge video → mark used (was `generate.py`) |
| `migrate_csv.py` | One-time helper to convert an old `quotes_pandas.csv` into the new schema |

## What was fixed / improved

1. **Schema mismatch bug** — the old `scrap.py` wrote only two Arabic-named
   columns (`الحكمة`, `الكاتب`), but `generate.py` expected `id`, `used`,
   and `date` columns too. Running the original two scripts back-to-back
   would have crashed on a `KeyError`. The new `scraper.py` writes the full
   schema (`id, quote, author, used, date`) that `pipeline.py` consumes.
2. **No error handling** — network calls, missing files, and subprocess
   failures now raise/log clear errors instead of crashing with a raw
   traceback or silently producing nothing.
3. **Logging instead of `print`** — timestamped log lines make it easier
   to tell what happened when running unattended (e.g. on a cron job).
4. **Duplicate TTS code** — `audio.py` and `generate.py` each had their
   own copy of `text_to_speech`. Consolidated into `tts.py`, imported by
   `pipeline.py`.
5. **`vedu.py` import bug** — `from moviepy.editor import ...` no longer
   exists in moviepy 2.0+. `video.py` tries the new import path first and
   falls back to the old one. The ffmpeg-based path (used by default) has
   no moviepy dependency at all, so this only matters if you opt into the
   `--engine moviepy` option.
6. **CLI arguments** — every script now takes `argparse` flags
   (`--csv`, `--url`, `--video`, `--all`, …) instead of hardcoded paths,
   so you don't have to edit source to point at different files.
7. **English throughout** — code, comments, and docstrings translated to
   English. Quote *content* stays Arabic since that's the actual data.

## Setup

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
# ffmpeg must also be installed on your system (used directly via subprocess)
```

## Usage

```bash
# 1. Scrape new quotes into quotes.csv
python scraper.py

# 2. (Once, only if you have an old quotes_pandas.csv) migrate it:
python migrate_csv.py quotes_pandas.csv quotes.csv

# 3. Put your background clip next to the scripts as background.mp4

# 4. Generate one video from the next unused quote
python pipeline.py

# ...or process every remaining quote in one go
python pipeline.py --all
```

Generated audio/video files land in `output/`, named by quote id
(e.g. `output/3.mp3`, `output/3.mp4`).